          },
          "tokens": [],
          "audio": {
            "playing": [
              "mus:0"
            ],
            "master": 0.8,
            "sfx": []
          }
        },
        "notes": "As you walk, you hear a commotion coming from the south. \n\nAs you look you see dust kicking up and a band of men jumping out of the tree line. A ragged band of brigands, faces hidden behind rough cloth, crude weapons in hand. They look lean and desperate, who prey on the weak and the strung-out. \n\nYou see them grabbing and threatening some of the travelers.\n\n\"Just the carts, just the coin, and nobody has to bleed.\"",
        "timeline": {
          "blackout": {
            "at": 0,
            "ramp": 2000
