        "notes": "A squat stone hut built into the gatehouse. This is where the gate officer records who passes and who is turned back, and where unusual travelers are taken aside to be questioned.\n\nInvestigation: On the desk lies the watch's refugee roster, a ledger of every name turned away at the gate. The Marsh family is the single entry held back rather than refused, marked for an audience. Beside it, in a different and hurried hand, a note set apart from the rest records that their matter was \"passed to the chancellery.\"",
